## Solution
I'll modify the swing detection logic to require 3-bar confirmation instead of 2-bar. This means a high/low must be higher/lower than both the previous AND next 2 bars to qualify as a swing point.

## Code
```javascript
// SwingAnalysis.jsx - Extract of detectSwings function
const detectSwings = (data) => {
  const swings = [];

  // Need at least 5 bars for 3-bar confirmation (2 before + current + 2 after)
  for (let i = 2; i < data.length - 2; i++) {
    const current = data[i];

    // Check for swing high: current high > both previous 2 highs AND next 2 highs
    const isSwingHigh = 
      current.high > data[i-1].high && 
      current.high > data[i-2].high && 
      current.high > data[i+1].high && 
      current.high > data[i+2].high;

    // Check for swing low: current low < both previous 2 lows AND next 2 lows
    const isSwingLow = 
      current.low < data[i-1].low && 
      current.low < data[i-2].low && 
      current.low < data[i+1].low && 
      current.low < data[i+2].low;

    if (isSwingHigh) {
      swings.push({
        index: i,
        time: current.time,
        price: current.high,
        type: 'high'
      });
    }

    if (isSwingLow) {
      swings.push({
        index: i,
        time: current.time,
        price: current.low,
        type: 'low'
      });
    }
  }

  return swings;
};
```

## Why
3-bar confirmation provides more reliable swing detection by ensuring the pivot point is truly a local extremum, reducing false signals common in volatile markets while maintaining simplicity for a 65+ institutional quant's preference.

